DTSTAMP:20260723T103547Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261006
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261007
SUMMARY:Deadline: Slamdance Film Festival 2027: DIG (Digital\, Interactive 
 and Gaming)
DESCRIPTION:Slamdance's DIG (Digital\, Interactive and Gaming) showcase pre
 sents work at the edges of cinema and interactivity: interactive documenta
 ries\, VR/AR\, experiential installations\, and experimental games\, a str
 ong fit for interactive AI and data-driven work. Film categories run on si
 milar deadline tiers. DIG deadlines: regular 10 August 2026 (USD 60)\, lat
 e 14 September 2026 (USD 70)\, extended 6 October 2026 (USD 90).\n\nOrgani
 sation: Slamdance\nLocation: Los Angeles\, California\, United States (fes
 tival 18-24 February 2027). Open to international entries.\nAward: Festiva
 l exhibition at Slamdance in Los Angeles. DIG welcomes interactive documen
 taries\, VR/AR\, experiential installations\, and genre-bending games. Ent
 ry fees: USD 60 regular\, USD 70 late\, USD 90 extended/final.\nDuration: 
 Festival 18-24 February 2027.\n\nMore: https://slamdance.com/festival-subm
 it/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://slamdance.com/festival-submit/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugran
 tdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Los Angeles\, California\, United States (festival 18-24 February 
 2027). Open to international entries.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:dc-festival-best-of-poland-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260723T103547Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260801
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260802
SUMMARY:Deadline: Digital Cultures Festival 2026: Best of Poland Open Call
DESCRIPTION:Best of Poland is the Digital Cultures Festival's showcase for 
 work at the intersection of art and technology. Open to anyone working cre
 atively in digital media (artists\, filmmakers\, game developers\, UX desi
 gners\, programmers\, curators\, students and more) with projects that sho
 w how technology fosters genuine human connection and addresses contempora
 ry social change. Eligible formats include VR\, AR\, interactive film\, ga
 mes\, net art and cross-media works\; both completed and in-progress proje
 cts qualify. Selected creators present 7-minute live pitches on 24 Septemb
 er 2026 in Warsaw\; the jury's top pick receives the Best of Poland Pitch 
 Award\, a career development grant of up to PLN 5\,000 funded by the Adam 
 Mickiewicz Institute to support participation in a European industry event
 \, and up to 10 creators receive pitch coaching with festival director Ann
 a Szylar and expert feedback. Free to apply via the form on the festival s
